1
00:00:01,174 --> 00:00:02,823
Previously on,

2
00:00:03,039 --> 00:00:05,778
I am determined to find someone
who wants to be with me

3
00:00:05,796 --> 00:00:08,004
for who I am,
not what I have.

4
00:00:08,025 --> 00:00:09,675
I need to buy
a little bit of everything.

5
00:00:09,692 --> 00:00:11,056
I can help you out with that.

6
00:00:11,073 --> 00:00:13,236
I appreciate it... Kate.

7
00:00:13,296 --> 00:00:15,113
Not a problem...

8
00:00:15,663 --> 00:00:16,805
Sam Wilson.

9
00:00:16,826 --> 00:00:18,567
It's refreshing,

10
00:00:18,595 --> 00:00:20,574
talking to someone like you
for a change.

11
00:00:20,590 --> 00:00:21,796
Someone like me?

12
00:00:21,810 --> 00:00:23,996
Yeah, someone who's not
constantly trying

13
00:00:24,010 --> 00:00:25,707
to impress me
with how much stuff he's got.

14
00:00:25,714 --> 00:00:27,876
Kate, this is
my friend Alan.

15
00:00:27,886 --> 00:00:29,762
Thanks so much
for picking us up.

16
00:00:29,775 --> 00:00:31,325
Yeah, this clown
rents a room from me,

17
00:00:31,337 --> 00:00:32,875
suddenly I'm running
a taxi service.

18
00:00:32,887 --> 00:00:34,193
You should move out.

19
00:00:34,202 --> 00:00:35,349
Can't afford to.

20
00:00:35,353 --> 00:00:37,021
Maybe you could crash here.

21
00:00:37,041 --> 00:00:38,136
Have you really
thought this through?

22
00:00:38,143 --> 00:00:39,977
I've got to see where
this goes with Kate.

23
00:00:39,992 --> 00:00:41,968
- Promise me one thing.
- What's that?

24
00:00:41,987 --> 00:00:44,313
That we're always honest
with each other.

25
00:00:44,346 --> 00:00:46,146
You got it.

26
00:00:47,982 --> 00:00:49,620
Anyways, I hope that it's okay

27
00:00:49,629 --> 00:00:50,973
that I have people over
on Christmas.

28
00:00:50,985 --> 00:00:52,997
It's just Jake
and Lyndsey and my mom.

29
00:00:53,009 --> 00:00:54,258
Of course.
It's the holidays.

30
00:00:54,267 --> 00:00:55,740
It's the time to be
with the ones you love.

31
00:00:55,751 --> 00:00:57,955
Right. Uh, and my mom.

32
00:00:58,675 --> 00:01:02,235
So, uh, so listen, Sam Wilson,
how are things in Poorville?

33
00:01:02,252 --> 00:01:04,019
Are you Les Misérables?

34
00:01:04,034 --> 00:01:05,938
Actually, it's a hoot.

35
00:01:07,742 --> 00:01:09,283
You know,
last night

36
00:01:09,299 --> 00:01:11,822
Kate and I went shopping
at the 99 Cent Store.

37
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,507
That place is amazing.

38
00:01:13,527 --> 00:01:16,130
Did you know that everything
there is 99 cents?

39
00:01:16,154 --> 00:01:19,316
Know it? I registered there
for my wedding.

40
00:01:19,347 --> 00:01:21,701
Two cans of peaches, 99 cents.

41
00:01:21,712 --> 00:01:24,147
Four-pack of yogurt, 99 cents.

42
00:01:24,324 --> 00:01:26,094
This owl-shaped mug?

43
00:01:26,113 --> 00:01:27,889
99 cents.

44
00:01:27,978 --> 00:01:29,688
Guess how much
the wine inside was?

45
00:01:29,702 --> 00:01:32,483
Uh, I'm going to go out
on a limb and say 99 cents?

46
00:01:32,507 --> 00:01:34,507
79 cents.

47
00:01:35,130 --> 00:01:36,938
Dented box.

48
00:01:36,976 --> 00:01:39,243
From now on, I'm buying
everything from that place.

49
00:01:39,254 --> 00:01:40,263
Uh, not condoms.

50
00:01:40,270 --> 00:01:42,666
I think that's how
I ended up with Jake.

51
00:01:43,373 --> 00:01:44,102
Hey.

52
00:01:44,127 --> 00:01:45,324
Hey, baby.

53
00:01:45,344 --> 00:01:46,510
Uh, I gotta go.

54
00:01:46,515 --> 00:01:47,848
Oh, hey, Katie.

55
00:01:47,871 --> 00:01:49,153
Alan.

56
00:01:49,188 --> 00:01:50,168
How are you?

57
00:01:50,183 --> 00:01:51,541
I'm fine— just, uh...

58
00:01:51,554 --> 00:01:54,689
sipping some wine I got
at the 999 Dollar Store.

59
00:01:55,871 --> 00:01:57,717
Bye, Alan.

60
00:01:57,812 --> 00:01:59,217
Douche.

61
00:01:59,438 --> 00:02:00,994
Don't worry about him.

62
00:02:01,127 --> 00:02:02,583
How was your day?

63
00:02:02,596 --> 00:02:04,343
It's Christmas, Sam.

64
00:02:04,375 --> 00:02:06,940
Happy people wishing you
"Peace on Earth."

65
00:02:06,962 --> 00:02:08,769
It was horrible.

66
00:02:08,796 --> 00:02:10,742
Okay, somebody's got
a case of the Grinches.

67
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:13,224
No, it's a case
of nine-hour shifts

68
00:02:13,245 --> 00:02:16,865
listening to Celine Dion
murder "O Holy Night."

69
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,467
If I ever meet
that skinny bitch,

70
00:02:18,481 --> 00:02:21,783
I'm going to beat
the "O Holy" crap out of her.

71
00:02:21,799 --> 00:02:23,825
And that's what Christmas
is all about.

72
00:02:25,184 --> 00:02:26,590
I'm sorry.

73
00:02:26,690 --> 00:02:28,040
Tell me about your day.

74
00:02:28,061 --> 00:02:30,728
After you left,
I made some breakfast...

75
00:02:30,752 --> 00:02:32,667
Oh, I got the mail.

76
00:02:32,695 --> 00:02:35,412
And then I did some work on
that app I've been developing,

77
00:02:35,443 --> 00:02:38,895
and then I did some serious
research on World War II.

78
00:02:38,912 --> 00:02:39,905
Really?

79
00:02:39,925 --> 00:02:42,247
Well, I fell asleep
watching the History Channel.

80
00:02:42,306 --> 00:02:44,131
Sweetie, can I be honest
with you?

81
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:45,423
Yeah. What's up?

82
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:48,217
I am working my ass off.

83
00:02:48,411 --> 00:02:51,292
It would be really,
really nice if you could,

84
00:02:51,626 --> 00:02:54,210
I don't know,
pitch in a little.

85
00:02:55,068 --> 00:02:57,823
You heard the part about me
getting the mail, right?

86
00:02:58,922 --> 00:03:01,624
You do understand that what came
in the mail is a pile of bills?

87
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:02,182
Okay...

88
00:03:02,189 --> 00:03:03,757
I mean, I think
it is great

89
00:03:03,764 --> 00:03:05,857
that you're working on
your computer stuff,

90
00:03:05,886 --> 00:03:07,552
but we need help now.

91
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,583
I get it.
Say no more.

92
00:03:09,845 --> 00:03:12,371
I'll start looking
for a job.

93
00:03:12,379 --> 00:03:13,494
Thank you.

94
00:03:13,656 --> 00:03:14,904
And don't worry,
it's not like

95
00:03:14,916 --> 00:03:16,211
I expect you to make
a million dollars or anything.

96
00:03:16,222 --> 00:03:17,975
Oh, thank God!

97
00:03:20,947 --> 00:03:23,278
Go ahead. I'm going
to go run a bath.

98
00:03:23,295 --> 00:03:25,727
I reek of comfort and joy.

99
00:03:27,984 --> 00:03:29,520
Hey, Billy. What's up?

100
00:03:29,541 --> 00:03:31,648
Nothing much—
just running our company

101
00:03:31,664 --> 00:03:33,869
while you take
some personal time.

102
00:03:33,884 --> 00:03:36,118
Why don't you just man up
and admit you're in rehab?

103
00:03:36,135 --> 00:03:37,590
I am not in rehab.

104
00:03:37,596 --> 00:03:40,147
I told you.
I'm on a spiritual journey.

105
00:03:40,165 --> 00:03:41,815
Spiritual journey.
Yeah, you know what?

106
00:03:41,830 --> 00:03:45,314
I've been on four of those.
I still wake up craving meth.

107
00:03:45,716 --> 00:03:48,042
I call it "Eat, Pray, Love,

108
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:50,987
Have Angry Sex
with an Asian Hooker."

109
00:03:51,015 --> 00:03:52,192
What do you want, Billy?

110
00:03:52,207 --> 00:03:53,436
Well, I'm just keeping
you in the loop

111
00:03:53,454 --> 00:03:54,753
about what's
going on around here.

112
00:03:54,771 --> 00:03:56,499
We got new computers
in the bullpen.

113
00:03:56,518 --> 00:03:58,169
We got a staple-less stapler.

114
00:03:58,182 --> 00:03:59,610
Mark Zuckerberg offered to buy

115
00:03:59,619 --> 00:04:01,536
a controlling interest
in the company for 800 million,

116
00:04:01,555 --> 00:04:04,925
and the redhead in marketing
is not wearing bras.

117
00:04:05,856 --> 00:04:07,421
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

118
00:04:07,860 --> 00:04:10,434
There's a staple-less stapler?

119
00:04:10,456 --> 00:04:12,510
I think we should
take his offer.

120
00:04:12,521 --> 00:04:15,269
Billy, we built the Electric
Suitcase from the ground up.

121
00:04:15,285 --> 00:04:17,359
I mean, besides,
we've been here before.

122
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:19,306
You hated the fact
that I sold our last company

123
00:04:19,325 --> 00:04:21,076
and I've come to realize
that you were right.

124
00:04:21,092 --> 00:04:23,711
I hated Tarnell, the gangsta
who sold me crack,

125
00:04:23,748 --> 00:04:25,998
but I was still happy
to work with him.

126
00:04:26,066 --> 00:04:27,841
I mean, look,
this is a good offer.

127
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:29,382
We should take it.

128
00:04:29,401 --> 00:04:30,294
Okay.

129
00:04:30,310 --> 00:04:33,494
Tell him 1.2 billion,
but we keep control.

130
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:35,801
Where do you think we're
going to get a better offer?

131
00:04:35,823 --> 00:04:37,892
Bath's ready.
Want to join me?

132
00:04:37,906 --> 00:04:40,470
I just got a better offer.
Good-bye.

