148
00:05:26,103 --> 00:05:28,200
What am I doing here
in my house?

149
00:05:28,209 --> 00:05:29,776
Uh, uh, I'm sorry.
Let me rephrase that.

150
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:32,173
Uh, uh, great to see you.
What brings you by?

151
00:05:32,194 --> 00:05:33,961
I'm doing laundry
for Kate and me.

152
00:05:33,968 --> 00:05:35,317
Really?
You did laundry.

153
00:05:35,329 --> 00:05:37,464
No, I did laundry.

154
00:05:38,103 --> 00:05:39,233
Thank you.

155
00:05:39,235 --> 00:05:41,351
So, you're, like,
some sort of kept man, huh?

156
00:05:41,368 --> 00:05:43,258
Well, I'm supposed
to be out job hunting,

157
00:05:43,273 --> 00:05:44,152
but it's kind of hard

158
00:05:44,163 --> 00:05:46,230
since Sam Wilson
doesn't actually exist.

159
00:05:46,256 --> 00:05:47,967
I can help you there.

160
00:05:47,988 --> 00:05:50,754
Five grand will get you
a clean Social Security card

161
00:05:50,777 --> 00:05:53,155
and a new set
of fingerprints.

162
00:05:53,582 --> 00:05:55,479
Six will get you
the fingers.

163
00:05:55,492 --> 00:05:56,807
The fingers?

164
00:05:56,829 --> 00:05:58,616
Better to have and not need

165
00:05:58,630 --> 00:06:00,805
than to need and not have.

166
00:06:03,679 --> 00:06:06,510
Hey, uh, why don't you
just go to an ATM,

167
00:06:06,535 --> 00:06:09,452
pull out a few thousand dollars
and tell her you got a job?

168
00:06:09,474 --> 00:06:10,952
But that would be lying.

169
00:06:11,099 --> 00:06:14,822
Oh, no, you wouldn't want
to lie to her, Sam Wilson.

170
00:06:14,852 --> 00:06:16,832
Let me explain something
to you, Alan.

171
00:06:16,843 --> 00:06:18,906
Walden Schmidt lies.

172
00:06:18,919 --> 00:06:21,203
Sam Wilson tells the truth.

173
00:06:21,228 --> 00:06:23,822
Besides, I like
Sam Wilson's life.

174
00:06:23,848 --> 00:06:27,094
It feels more like...
I don't know, real life.

175
00:06:27,116 --> 00:06:28,605
Yeah, I get that.

176
00:06:28,615 --> 00:06:30,458
I mean, that's why I like
to sleep in your bed.

177
00:06:30,464 --> 00:06:32,719
Feels more like a real bed.

178
00:06:33,185 --> 00:06:34,530
Oh, and get this.

179
00:06:34,537 --> 00:06:36,049
I got a call from Billy today.

180
00:06:36,089 --> 00:06:40,141
We got an offer to buy
our company for $800 million.

181
00:06:43,295 --> 00:06:44,829
Excuse me a sec.

182
00:06:58,546 --> 00:07:00,731
$800 million?

183
00:07:02,303 --> 00:07:03,854
Yeah, We turned it down.

184
00:07:03,868 --> 00:07:05,596
You turned it down.

185
00:07:18,454 --> 00:07:19,935
Check it out.

186
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:22,360
Oh, Sam!

187
00:07:22,371 --> 00:07:24,357
I hope you stole that.

188
00:07:24,552 --> 00:07:26,375
Ah, it wasn't that expensive.

189
00:07:26,383 --> 00:07:28,520
We barely made rent this month.

190
00:07:28,547 --> 00:07:30,699
I know,
but it's Christmas.

191
00:07:30,717 --> 00:07:32,661
You don't have to tell me.

192
00:07:32,677 --> 00:07:33,827
I'm earning extra money

193
00:07:33,839 --> 00:07:37,007
by making a Santa outfit
for my boss' Labradoodle.

194
00:07:37,019 --> 00:07:38,225
Aw, that's cute.

195
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,565
Yeah, then I'm going to make

196
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:42,081
three wise men costumes
for her cats.

197
00:07:42,299 --> 00:07:45,266
And just like that,
cute becomes creepy.

198
00:07:45,816 --> 00:07:47,452
Okay, I'm going
to go change.

199
00:07:47,463 --> 00:07:48,791
I've got a lead
on a job.

200
00:07:48,798 --> 00:07:49,780
- Really?
- Yeah.

201
00:07:49,790 --> 00:07:52,052
If that doesn't work,
I'm going to rob a bank.

202
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:55,206
I hope the 99 Cent Store
sells ski masks.

203
00:07:57,176 --> 00:07:59,978
- Oh, man.
- What?

204
00:08:00,015 --> 00:08:02,594
I forgot to give Santa
a tail-hole.

205
00:08:02,876 --> 00:08:05,507
Worst Christmas carol ever.

206
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:14,092
- Hey, Dad.
- Hey, buddy.

207
00:08:14,108 --> 00:08:15,391
You excited about Christmas?

208
00:08:15,407 --> 00:08:17,644
Yeah, that's actually
why I was calling.

209
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:19,648
I'm not going to be able
to make it home this year.

210
00:08:19,670 --> 00:08:21,180
What? Why?

211
00:08:21,190 --> 00:08:22,432
My girlfriend Tammy Sue

212
00:08:22,446 --> 00:08:24,780
asked me to spend Christmas
with her and her three kids.

213
00:08:24,795 --> 00:08:26,067
I'm pretending to be Santa

214
00:08:26,074 --> 00:08:28,175
and also their various fathers.

215
00:08:28,563 --> 00:08:30,262
Oh, kill me.

216
00:08:30,461 --> 00:08:32,217
H-H-How did you meet this woman?

217
00:08:32,231 --> 00:08:34,876
I play softball
with her parole officer.

218
00:08:35,016 --> 00:08:37,787
Oh, dig me up and kill me again.

219
00:08:38,996 --> 00:08:41,739
All right, well,
I hope I see you soon.

220
00:08:41,755 --> 00:08:43,246
Don't worry—
we'll all come visit

221
00:08:43,261 --> 00:08:45,678
as soon as Tammy Sue
gets her ankle bracelet off.

222
00:08:46,024 --> 00:08:48,416
That will be a magical day.

223
00:08:48,738 --> 00:08:49,596
Yeah.

224
00:08:49,611 --> 00:08:51,841
Well, all right—
Merry Christmas, Dad. Bye.

225
00:08:51,851 --> 00:08:53,888
Merry Christmas, Jake.

226
00:08:56,519 --> 00:08:59,628
Time now
for the magic of bourbon.

227
00:09:01,636 --> 00:09:02,669
Hi.

228
00:09:02,996 --> 00:09:05,300
I was here earlier.
I bought a tree.

229
00:09:05,307 --> 00:09:08,224
Uh, I was hoping I could talk
to you about something else.

230
00:09:08,241 --> 00:09:10,229
If somebody told you
I'm selling pot here,

231
00:09:10,248 --> 00:09:12,540
that is just crazy talk.

232
00:09:12,738 --> 00:09:14,104
Uh, no.

233
00:09:14,131 --> 00:09:16,598
I saw the "help wanted" sign.
I was hoping to get a job.

234
00:09:16,619 --> 00:09:18,823
Oh. Have a seat.

235
00:09:19,704 --> 00:09:22,229
You got any, uh,
Christmas tree experience?

236
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,793
I-I've decorated a bunch.

237
00:09:27,176 --> 00:09:28,926
Experience, none.

238
00:09:29,451 --> 00:09:31,567
It's... Wait, it's selling
Christmas trees.

239
00:09:31,588 --> 00:09:33,117
Pop quiz, hot shot.

240
00:09:33,132 --> 00:09:34,964
A mom walks in;
she's driving a Lexus.

241
00:09:34,987 --> 00:09:36,725
She's got a big living room,
cathedral ceiling.

242
00:09:36,730 --> 00:09:37,659
What are you pushing?

243
00:09:37,672 --> 00:09:39,681
Balsam? Noble?
Doug fir?

244
00:09:39,697 --> 00:09:40,787
Uh...

245
00:09:40,799 --> 00:09:43,203
You're out of time.
She's across the street

246
00:09:43,215 --> 00:09:44,639
buying a 20-footer...

247
00:09:44,657 --> 00:09:46,369
from the Armenian.

248
00:09:48,552 --> 00:09:50,655
Are you comfortable
with celebrities?

249
00:09:50,845 --> 00:09:51,955
What do you mean?

250
00:09:51,961 --> 00:09:53,282
We get a lot of big names.

251
00:09:53,294 --> 00:09:55,517
Mario Lopez buys
his tree here every year.

252
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:57,927
I don't want you getting
all jelly-legged.

253
00:09:58,170 --> 00:09:59,117
All right, look.

254
00:09:59,135 --> 00:10:01,607
I'm young, I'm strong,
and I need the money.

255
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:03,944
I'll work really hard
and I won't let you down.

256
